	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Wed Sep 18, 2013 11:30 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Please Help me Understand This Schematic Portion</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Optoisolator_Pinout.svg">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Opto ... Pinout.svg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />There isn't a symbol for &quot;this signal is isolated&quot;, just the actual use of it.<br /><br />The MIDI OUT jack should be have its shield grounded, so that the cable's shield is grounded on the transmitting side. The receving side should have an optoisolator from current source (pin 4) to current sink (pin 5) and not be in any other way connected.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>infiniteneslives</b> [ Thu Sep 19, 2013 10:47 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Please Help me Understand This Schematic Portion</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">bazz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What confused me is that, MIDI IN is a Port, not a cable.<br /><br />Perhaps they just did it this way to convey that the cable portion is grounded.<br /><br />So do I not need to worry about shielding once the cable plugs into the port and i build the circuit?</div><br /><br />The outer metalic circular ring should be grounded, so that the outer sheild of the cable is grounded when connected to your port.  That's usually the large chassis like portion of your port, the big leads that fix it to the circuit board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


